Corrected code:
def fib(n, memo=None):
    if memo is None:
        memo = {}
    if n in memo:
        return memo[n]
    if n <= 1:
        result = n
    else:
        result = fib(n-1, memo) + fib(n-2, memo)
    memo[n] = result
    return result

Explanation: The recursive calls now pass the memo dictionary so memoization persists through deeper calls, preventing redundant computations.

