Memoization is a technique where you cache the results of expensive function calls so that future calls with the same inputs can reuse the result instead of recomputing. It speeds up repeated calculations. Example:

def fib(n, cache=None):
  if cache is None:
    cache = {0: 0, 1: 1}
  if n in cache:
    return cache[n]
  cache[n] = fib(n-1, cache) + fib(n-2, cache)
  return cache[n]

